Snap tools hotkeys. 

To toggle on/off with the top regular menu is to use ctrl and m. 

To toggle on/off with the blue highlighted regular menu is to use shift and m. 

To toggle on/off with the viewport top menu is to use ctrl, shift and m(but I prefer keeping it). 

To temporary use snap to grid, snap to curve, and snap to point(vertice) is to use x, c, v, respectively. 

Viewport modes hotkeys 

Press 4, 5, 6, 7 to enter wireframe mode, shaded mode, textured mode, and lighting mode. 

Ignore shaded mode will do us a benefit that we would not forget to turn on textured mode when we do textures since textured mode is shaded mode with texture on it. 

Lighting mode is for rendering which we only do in Unity, marmoset, or substance painter/designer, but not in Maya. 

And one more tip, ctrl and 1 is isolated mode.
